PackageProperties Class

In this Article

Represents the core properties of a Package.

Syntax

public abstract class PackageProperties : IDisposable

Properties summary

Category

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the category of the Package.
ContentStatus

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that represents the status of the Package.
ContentType

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that represents the type of content that is contained in the Package.
Created

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the date and time the Package was created.
Creator

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that identifies the individual or entity that created the Package and its content.
Description

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a description of the content contained in the Package.
Identifier

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that unambiguously identifies the Package and its content.
Keywords

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that define a delimited set of keywords to support searching and indexing the Package and its content.
Language

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that identifies the language of the Package content.
LastModifiedBy

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that identifies the user who last modified the Package content.
LastPrinted

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the date and time the Package content was last printed.
Modified

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the date and time the Package was last changed.
Revision

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the revision number of the Package.
Subject

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the topic of the Package content.
Title

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the name given to the Package and its content.
Version

When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the version number of the Package.

Constructors

  • PackageProperties()

    Initializes a new instance of the PackageProperties class.

    protected PackageProperties ();

Properties

  • Category

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the category of the Package.

    public abstract string Category { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The category of the content that is contained in the Package.

    Remarks

    The Category value is typically used as part of the application user interface (UI) to create labels for navigation controls.

  • ContentStatus

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that represents the status of the Package.

    public abstract string ContentStatus { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The status of the Package content.

    Remarks

    Example ContentStatus values include "Draft", "Reviewed", and "Final".

  • ContentType

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that represents the type of content that is contained in the Package.

    public abstract string ContentType { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The type of content that is contained in the Package.

    Remarks

    Example ContentType values include "Whitepaper", "Security Bulletin", and "Exam".

    This ContentType property is distinct from Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) content types as defined in RFC 2616.

  • Created

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the date and time the Package was created.

    public abstract Nullable<DateTime> Created { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • Nullable<DateTime>

      The date and time the Package was initially created.

  • Creator

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that identifies the individual or entity that created the Package and its content.

    public abstract string Creator { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The individual or entity that created the Package and its content.

  • Description

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a description of the content contained in the Package.

    public abstract string Description { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A description of the content contained in the Package.

    Remarks

    The Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, table of contents, reference to a graphical representation of content, or a free-text account of the content.

  • Identifier

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that unambiguously identifies the Package and its content.

    public abstract string Identifier { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A value that unambiguously identifies the Package and its content.

  • Keywords

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that define a delimited set of keywords to support searching and indexing the Package and its content.

    public abstract string Keywords { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A delimited set of keywords to support searching and indexing the Package and content.

    Remarks

    The Keywords property typically contains a list of terms that are not available elsewhere in PackageProperties.

  • Language

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that identifies the language of the Package content.

    public abstract string Language { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A value that identifies the Package content language.

  • LastModifiedBy

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value that identifies the user who last modified the Package content.

    public abstract string LastModifiedBy { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The user who last modified the Package content.

  • LastPrinted

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the date and time the Package content was last printed.

    public abstract Nullable<DateTime> LastPrinted { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • Nullable<DateTime>

      The date and time the Package content was last printed.

  • Modified

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the date and time the Package was last changed.

    public abstract Nullable<DateTime> Modified { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • Nullable<DateTime>

      The date and time the Package was last changed.

  • Revision

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the revision number of the Package.

    public abstract string Revision { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The revision number of the Package.

    Remarks

    The Revision property indicates the number of changed saves or revisions.

    The application is responsible for updating the Revision property value after each revision.

  • Subject

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the topic of the Package content.

    public abstract string Subject { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The topic of the Package content.

  • Title

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the name given to the Package and its content.

    public abstract string Title { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The name given to the Package and its content.

  • Version

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the version number of the Package.

    public abstract string Version { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The version number of the Package.

Methods

  • Dispose()

    Releases all resources used by the PackageProperties instance.

    public void Dispose ();

    Remarks

    Call Dispose when you are finished using the PackageProperties. The Dispose method leaves the PackageProperties in an unusable state. After calling Dispose, you must release all references to the PackageProperties so the garbage collector can reclaim the memory that the PackageProperties was occupying. For more information, see Cleaning Up Unmanaged Resources and Implementing a Dispose Method.

    Note

    Always call Dispose before you release your last reference to the PackageProperties. Otherwise, the resources it is using will not be freed until the garbage collector calls the PackageProperties object's Finalize method.

  • Dispose(Boolean)

    Releases the unmanaged resources used by the PackageProperties instance and optionally releases the managed resources.

    protected virtual void Dispose (bool disposing);

    Parameters

    • disposing
      Boolean

      true to release both managed and unmanaged resources; false to release only unmanaged resources.

    Remarks

    This method is called by the public Dispose()method and the Finalize method. Dispose() invokes the protected Dispose(Boolean) method with the disposing parameter set to true. Finalize invokes Dispose with disposing set to false.

    When the disposing parameter is true, this method releases all resources held by any managed objects that this PackageProperties references. This method invokes the Dispose() method of each referenced object.
